          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Small Business Acquisition Transparency Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill requires a federal contracting officer, upon written request from an unsuccessful offeror for a task order or delivery order, to provide a brief explanation as to why such offeror was unsuccessful. </p> <p>Specifically, this applies to an offer in an amount greater than the simplified acquisition threshold and less than or equal to $5.5 million issued under an indefinite delivery-indefinite quantity contract.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-07-09T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
